      "content": "exactly. the \"noise\" is just constant. everything is just more expectations and more trying to fix things that are clearly broken beyond repair. it feels like the only way to actually get that silence and stop the exhaustion is to just... stop. to just opt out of the whole mess. it feels like the only way to find any real quiet is to not be here to hear the noise anymore. does that even make sense? that the only way to truly rest is to just not exist?",
